31
00:02:55,435 --> 00:02:58,716
So like you said, I work for the Somerville Homeless Coalition.

32
00:02:59,416 --> 00:03:04,518
It's a really small nonprofit in Somerville, but we serve a lot of people.

33
00:03:04,598 --> 00:03:09,380
We serve, you know, pretty much all greater Boston.

34
00:03:09,460 --> 00:03:11,861
We're part of what's called the balance of state.

35
00:03:11,881 --> 00:03:14,042
So we're not really just stuck to Somerville.

36
00:03:14,142 --> 00:03:17,943
We do take a regional approach to serving people experiencing homelessness.

37
00:03:18,685 --> 00:03:21,706
as well as people on the brink of homelessness.

38
00:03:22,546 --> 00:03:27,127
So my particular role there is called the Emergency Services Program Manager.

39
00:03:28,168 --> 00:03:31,429
So I kind of have two focuses.

40
00:03:31,709 --> 00:03:40,171
My main one is to supervise and kind of control the daily operations of our two shelters.

41
00:03:41,032 --> 00:03:45,893
So we have an individual shelter and a state funded family shelter.

42
00:03:46,793 --> 00:04:03,338
And then the second part of my job is to oversee our street outreach program, where we're going out into encampments in the area, hitting the streets where people are sleeping at night, kind of the most vulnerable homeless people that we see, and really trying to engage with them.

43
00:04:03,358 --> 00:04:06,659
So that's what I do.

44
00:04:08,219 --> 00:04:09,139
That is great.

45
00:04:09,359 --> 00:04:10,400
Really needed work.

46
00:04:12,062 --> 00:04:21,811
