335
00:29:34,056 --> 00:29:37,839
So we've gotten better about reduce, reuse, recycle.

336
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:44,244
And what I would say is a lot of these masks and gowns were designed to be disposable.

337
00:29:44,925 --> 00:29:47,587
And what we're finding is we have to find a better way.

338
00:29:48,427 --> 00:29:56,113
And what we've done is there are washable, waterproof lab coats that we can use throughout a shift.

339
00:29:56,754 --> 00:30:01,077
And 95 masks, instead of changing them with each patient, we're using them throughout a shift

340
00:30:01,715 --> 00:30:03,216
then they're being decontaminated.

341
00:30:03,456 --> 00:30:09,838
So I believe all the hospitals are decontaminating their N95 masks so they can be used up to 20 times.

342
00:30:09,858 --> 00:30:10,379
Wow.

343
00:30:10,859 --> 00:30:13,340
Now this is a huge change.

344
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:18,722
As long as it's safe to do this is amazing because then we don't need to buy millions of masks.

345
00:30:19,162 --> 00:30:23,084
We just need to safely decontaminate them and then get them back into circulation.

